caption: Do you have to come in here every time I turn on the light?
I really hope you make better use of your last two wishes.
What the hell is a midlife chrysalis?
You know I can't stand it when you hover.
Ok, fine. You are capable of change.
This wasn’t what I meant when I told you to grow a pair.
You went out for wings without me?
It’s 2 AM and once again you flit home reeking of pollen and nectar.
Oh God, you caught the variant.
Good, now why don't you go check on that porch light?
I see that you’re finally over your mid-life chrysalis.
Well, look who thinks he’s the new monarch around here.
That's not what I meant when I told you to "Grow a pair"
I thought you were European when you said your family came from monarchs.
I give up. New glasses?
When you told me you were transitioning, this isn't what I expected.
When I told you to grow a pair, this is not what I had in mind.
For goodness’s sake, Robert, there’s no reason to come downstairs every time I turn the lamp on
« Go and enjoy the lights if you must, but if you are not back by 11:30 you’re sleeping on the screen door again »
You're not the caterpillar I married.
Shouldn’t you be in Mexico by now?
This is not what I meant by "grow a pair".
So, it’s off to Mexico again, is it?
Howard, I don’t care if you’ve only got one day to breed. The answer is still No.
What is your preferred pronoun now?
When you said you were transitioning, this is not what came to my mind
Yeah, well I sting like a bee so finish cleaning the dishes.
This insert says it's one of the 'very rare' side effects.
You know George, most people turn 50 and just buy a motorcycle.
The Very Hungry Butterfly can make his own sandwich.
